    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n#39845 adds the line (`l`) text as a characterwise text object.\n\nFor the sake of simplicity, it does not use a count to grow across multiple lines.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n***NOTE***: More discussion for the \"proper\" behavior is warranted. Leave your input - below is just some of my preliminary ideas:\n\n`[count]il` could extend the `l` text object across multiple lines. Intervening line breaks should be preserved while the final trailing line break remains excluded (just like `g_` over multiple lines).\n\nNot too sure about blank/whitespace only lines - any ideas?\n\n`al` is not impacted.",
